1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:40,000
( Watch on www.kissasia.co, .club, .be, .org, .net, .id, .xyz )

2
00:00:42,764 --> 00:00:43,804
[This drama is a work of fiction.]

3
00:00:43,804 --> 00:00:44,858
[Any resemblance to real persons,
places, or events is coincidental.]

4
00:00:44,858 --> 00:00:45,875
[Scenes with child actors and animals
were filmed safely]

5
00:00:45,875 --> 00:00:47,068
[under professional supervision.]

6
00:01:13,758 --> 00:01:16,104
You

7
00:01:16,104 --> 00:01:19,111
just wanted to use me

8
00:01:20,560 --> 00:01:24,147
for your grand ambition.

9
00:01:28,568 --> 00:01:31,509
Do you get it now?

10
00:01:31,509 --> 00:01:34,309
This is your last chance.

11
00:01:34,989 --> 00:01:37,789
You choose.

12
00:01:39,871 --> 00:01:42,791
Either you or me...

13
00:01:43,875 --> 00:01:47,254
If this goes any further,

14
00:01:48,204 --> 00:01:51,736
it won't end with someone getting hurt.

15
00:02:01,476 --> 00:02:05,689
I did everything I could to protect you,

16
00:02:07,274 --> 00:02:10,736
but maybe I chose the wrong way.

17
00:04:06,393 --> 00:04:08,466
[Danger: High Voltage]
[Authorized Personnel Only]

18
00:04:55,829 --> 00:04:58,529
Mr. Bang Tae Seop.

19
00:04:58,529 --> 00:05:01,165
What you're about to do

20
00:05:01,165 --> 00:05:04,362
is kill the dead a second time.

21
00:05:08,557 --> 00:05:11,690
But once you see this through,

22
00:05:11,690 --> 00:05:13,441
you'll rise all the way to the top,

23
00:05:13,441 --> 00:05:16,947
just like you wanted.

24
00:05:18,769 --> 00:05:22,155
But in return...

25
00:05:24,400 --> 00:05:26,023
You'll have to give up

26
00:05:26,023 --> 00:05:29,896
the one thing you value most.

27
00:05:34,852 --> 00:05:37,546
For example...

28
00:05:44,128 --> 00:05:47,095
Chu Sang Ah.

29
00:05:52,443 --> 00:05:55,003
Fine.

30
00:05:55,863 --> 00:05:58,909
Then I'll be the one who dies.

31
00:06:13,395 --> 00:06:15,197
[Episode 1]

32
00:06:21,444 --> 00:06:25,407
I was born the son of a factory worker.

33
00:06:25,407 --> 00:06:27,975
My father was a union leader.

34
00:06:27,975 --> 00:06:30,269
While fighting for the workers' rights,

35
00:06:30,269 --> 00:06:32,065
he was handed a prison sentence

36
00:06:32,065 --> 00:06:35,016
by the prosecutor on the case,
a man who had taken bribes from the company.

37
00:06:35,016 --> 00:06:36,362
[Steel Mill Union Leader Bang's Tragic Death:
Will the Truth Ever Come Out?]

38
00:06:36,362 --> 00:06:37,468
And that night...

39
00:06:37,468 --> 00:06:40,639
he took his own life.

40
00:06:46,221 --> 00:06:49,294
I wanted revenge.

41
00:06:53,576 --> 00:06:57,029
That's why I became a prosecutor.

42
00:06:57,029 --> 00:07:00,036
But that place...

43
00:07:00,036 --> 00:07:02,467
was their own private kingdom.

44
00:07:02,467 --> 00:07:04,007
[Stay strong today and tomorrow, too.]

45
00:07:08,383 --> 00:07:11,679
To squeeze in among the bloodlines
that run the legal world,

46
00:07:11,679 --> 00:07:13,106
I even emptied my rent money

47
00:07:13,106 --> 00:07:15,039
to buy a Mercedes-benz,

48
00:07:15,039 --> 00:07:17,376
and crashed at my sister's hair salon.

49
00:07:17,376 --> 00:07:20,477
[Seong Hye Hair Salon]

50
00:07:24,883 --> 00:07:27,229
I even tried getting in
with the chief prosecutor's circle.

51
00:07:27,229 --> 00:07:28,820
Once, I hung off

52
00:07:28,820 --> 00:07:30,504
a ninth-floor hotel railing

53
00:07:30,504 --> 00:07:34,785
for five hours in eight-below-zero weather.

54
00:07:34,785 --> 00:07:37,652
But nothing changed.

55
00:07:41,898 --> 00:07:43,568
Come on.

56
00:07:43,568 --> 00:07:45,353
Knock it off.

57
00:07:45,353 --> 00:07:48,946
You really think that'll get you in
with those true-blood elites?

58
00:07:48,946 --> 00:07:50,399
Well...

59
00:07:50,399 --> 00:07:51,923
The more desperate you are,

60
00:07:51,923 --> 00:07:53,983
the easier it is for them
to squeeze you dry and toss you aside.

61
00:07:53,983 --> 00:07:57,192
That's how the prosecution works.

62
00:07:57,192 --> 00:08:00,502
I wanted to stand above the world

63
00:08:00,502 --> 00:08:03,792
and look down on them.

64
00:08:03,792 --> 00:08:06,076
I needed the key

65
00:08:06,076 --> 00:08:09,229
that could open the gates to that kingdom.

66
00:08:20,600 --> 00:08:23,320
Chu Sang Ah.

67
00:08:49,008 --> 00:08:50,453
In the end,

68
00:08:50,453 --> 00:08:54,818
I met her when she came in
for questioning as a witness.

69
00:09:22,674 --> 00:09:26,160
It was the perfect opportunity

70
00:09:26,160 --> 00:09:28,598
to make the world know my name.

71
00:09:28,598 --> 00:09:30,222
[Top Actress Chu Sang Ah Announces Marriage]

72
00:09:30,222 --> 00:09:33,707
The relationship between a dirt-poor prosecutor
and a pop star who once swept across Asia

73
00:09:33,707 --> 00:09:35,171
is being called
Korea's version of "Notting Hill,"

74
00:09:35,171 --> 00:09:36,684
a marriage of the century

75
00:09:36,684 --> 00:09:41,144
that has captured the nation
like a real-life romance drama.

76
00:09:46,858 --> 00:09:49,694
[Top Star Chu Sang Ah Suspected of
Multi-Billion-Won Tax Evasion]

77
00:09:49,694 --> 00:09:52,232
[The Fall of the Nation's Actress]

78
00:09:52,232 --> 00:09:54,810
[Despite her heartfelt apology,
public reaction remains cold]

79
00:09:54,810 --> 00:09:56,687
Today, we have someone,

80
00:09:56,687 --> 00:09:59,641
who has stood by my side for many years

81
00:09:59,641 --> 00:10:02,255
[Chu Sang Ah After Tax Evasion Scandal]
and endured this harsh industry with me.

82
00:10:02,255 --> 00:10:03,677
[Spotted at Co-CEO's Child's Birthday Party]
Our nation's beloved actress.

83
00:10:03,677 --> 00:10:07,231
Please welcome Chu Sang Ah.

84
00:10:11,545 --> 00:10:13,689
Come out here for a moment.

85
00:10:13,689 --> 00:10:15,476
[She looks flustered]
It's okay.

86
00:10:15,476 --> 00:10:18,616
Let's give her a round of applause.

87
00:10:19,852 --> 00:10:21,817
- Please sing a song for us.
- Please!

88
00:10:21,817 --> 00:10:23,576
[She's aged a lot since we last saw her]
Sing for us.

89
00:10:23,576 --> 00:10:26,102
Sing! Sing!

90
00:10:26,102 --> 00:10:28,686
Sing! Sing!

91
00:10:28,686 --> 00:10:30,739
Give a big hand!

92
00:10:54,550 --> 00:10:59,306
[Chu Sang Ah After Tax Evasion Scandal]

93
00:11:14,063 --> 00:11:18,696
I told you not to watch that.

94
00:11:18,696 --> 00:11:20,346
Mi Soon.

95
00:11:20,346 --> 00:11:22,250
Yes?

96
00:11:22,250 --> 00:11:25,506
Is the person who filmed and
posted that video the problem?

97
00:11:25,506 --> 00:11:29,666
Or the people next to them
bluntly calling it out?

98
00:11:31,512 --> 00:11:34,423
Or is the problem me, a has-been past my prime?

99
00:11:34,423 --> 00:11:36,571
Come on, of course not.

100
00:11:36,571 --> 00:11:40,054
- Past your prime? Don't say that.
- Then what, ancient?

101
00:11:40,054 --> 00:11:42,849
You're kidding, right?

102
00:11:45,910 --> 00:11:49,650
Look at these fine lines.

103
00:11:49,650 --> 00:11:50,867
Touch this up for me.

104
00:11:50,867 --> 00:11:53,240
Today my makeup has to look natural.

105
00:11:53,240 --> 00:11:55,433
Okay?

106
00:11:58,118 --> 00:12:04,203
♪ The moment you stood by my side ♪

107
00:12:04,203 --> 00:12:09,042
♪ I love that look in your eyes ♪

108
00:12:11,377 --> 00:12:14,255
♪ Yesterday I cried ♪

109
00:12:14,255 --> 00:12:16,132
♪ But today, because of you ♪

110
00:12:16,132 --> 00:12:17,800
♪ tomorrow I'll be happy ♪

111
00:12:17,800 --> 00:12:21,007
- I'll be happy!
- I'll be happy!

112
00:12:22,426 --> 00:12:27,756
♪ Eat plenty today and have a drink ♪

113
00:12:27,756 --> 00:12:32,015
♪ All I ever needed was a gentle love ♪

114
00:12:32,015 --> 00:12:41,530
♪ So I could forget all the years gone by ♪

115
00:12:41,530 --> 00:12:43,674
♪ Without you ♪

116
00:12:43,674 --> 00:12:48,708
♪ I can't do anything anymore ♪

117
00:12:48,708 --> 00:12:53,434
♪ All I know is love ♪

118
00:12:54,712 --> 00:12:57,650
[Assemblymember Kwak Jung Ja]

119
00:13:00,401 --> 00:13:03,032
Let me first offer my sincere birthday wishes

120
00:13:03,032 --> 00:13:06,751
to our beloved Changjo Party's
Assemblywoman Kwak Jung Ja.

121
00:13:06,751 --> 00:13:07,995
I couldn't just pass by,

122
00:13:07,995 --> 00:13:10,981
so I stopped in for a moment
while I was next door.

123
00:13:10,981 --> 00:13:13,221
I'm Bang Tae Seop, the star prosecutor of

124
00:13:13,221 --> 00:13:15,781
Seoul Central District Prosecutors' Office,
Criminal Division 3.

125
00:13:15,781 --> 00:13:18,181
Thank you.

126
00:13:23,001 --> 00:13:25,585
Prosecutor Bang,
you should pour me a drink before you go.

127
00:13:25,585 --> 00:13:26,998
Of course.

128
00:13:26,998 --> 00:13:30,318
Let me pour you a nice strong one.

129
00:13:39,765 --> 00:13:41,408
He's good.

130
00:13:41,408 --> 00:13:44,641
Happy birthday.

131
00:13:45,867 --> 00:13:49,741
- Congratulations.
- Thank you.

132
00:14:15,001 --> 00:14:16,233
[Stay strong today and tomorrow, too.]

133
00:14:16,233 --> 00:14:20,141
Top stars always fade eventually.

134
00:14:20,882 --> 00:14:25,225
And now that the perks he enjoyed
thanks to his wife have run out,

135
00:14:25,225 --> 00:14:28,585
he probably doesn't see a future
in this office and wants out.

136
00:14:28,585 --> 00:14:33,351
Yeah, I'm getting out of
the District Prosecutors' Office.

137
00:14:35,718 --> 00:14:37,464
So,

138
00:14:37,464 --> 00:14:39,834
what exactly are you planning to do?

139
00:14:39,834 --> 00:14:44,274
If you roll and crawl your way somewhere
only to find it's a sewer,

140
00:14:44,274 --> 00:14:46,924
then you find another hole to crawl into.

141
00:14:46,924 --> 00:14:48,624
Fair enough.

142
00:14:48,624 --> 00:14:52,460
You got an offer
from the Changjo Party before, right?

143
00:14:52,460 --> 00:14:54,338
Instead of rotting away here,

144
00:14:54,338 --> 00:14:58,305
try getting nominated
for this year's general election.

145
00:15:01,447 --> 00:15:03,231
As the general election is three months away

146
00:15:03,231 --> 00:15:04,780
and the presidential election
just over a year out,

147
00:15:04,780 --> 00:15:08,401
attention is focused on the next moves of
Mayor of Seoam, Nam Hye Hoon.

148
00:15:08,401 --> 00:15:11,095
She continues to lead in polls
measuring public support

149
00:15:11,095 --> 00:15:13,918
for the opposition's next political leader.

150
00:15:13,918 --> 00:15:16,508
She recently gave an exclusive interview
to The London Times,

151
00:15:16,508 --> 00:15:19,628
the first ever by Mayor of Seoam,

152
00:15:19,628 --> 00:15:22,492
showcasing her presence as a global leader.

153
00:15:22,492 --> 00:15:24,516
Nam Hye Hoon.

154
00:15:24,516 --> 00:15:27,273
What if she actually makes it
to the Blue House at this rate?

155
00:15:27,273 --> 00:15:28,860
Hey.

156
00:15:28,860 --> 00:15:31,324
You do know she's a sewer, right?

157
00:15:31,324 --> 00:15:34,038
Don't say something so horrifying.

158
00:15:34,038 --> 00:15:35,320
About Senior Prosecutor Yoon...

159
00:15:35,320 --> 00:15:38,461
You know he got cut off
while digging into her, right?

160
00:15:38,461 --> 00:15:40,731
- Did he?
- Yeah.

161
00:15:40,731 --> 00:15:44,590
The case where Mayor Nam took kickbacks from TM
and pushed through that redevelopment deal.

162
00:15:44,590 --> 00:15:46,582
He was digging into it and
got caught by the Chief Prosecutor.

163
00:15:46,582 --> 00:15:48,631
That's when his head rolled.

164
00:15:48,631 --> 00:15:51,734
Mayor Nam is the Chief Prosecutor's in-law.

165
00:15:51,734 --> 00:15:53,608
Darn it.

166
00:15:53,608 --> 00:15:56,232
But Joong Hyuk
was in the Chief Prosecutor's line.

167
00:15:56,232 --> 00:15:58,885
Line or not, he still got thrown under the bus.

168
00:15:58,885 --> 00:16:00,909
Anyway, Mayor Nam

169
00:16:00,909 --> 00:16:02,733
is a hot potato right now.

170
00:16:02,733 --> 00:16:04,360
Everyone thinks if they dig up something
and blow it open,

171
00:16:04,360 --> 00:16:05,821
they'll get the spotlight

172
00:16:05,821 --> 00:16:08,066
and land a job at a big law firm
or go into politics.

173
00:16:08,066 --> 00:16:10,099
But they all jump in,

174
00:16:10,099 --> 00:16:12,224
get crushed, get blacklisted,

175
00:16:12,224 --> 00:16:15,265
and end up doing public defense
for the rest of their lives.

176
00:16:15,265 --> 00:16:18,624
It's a poisoned chalice.

177
00:16:33,968 --> 00:16:35,479
Hey, it's been a while.

178
00:16:35,479 --> 00:16:37,932
Hello, Mi Soon.

179
00:16:37,932 --> 00:16:39,383
Nice haircut.

180
00:16:39,383 --> 00:16:41,092
You have a good sense, as always.

181
00:16:41,092 --> 00:16:43,082
Good work today, Mi Soon.

182
00:16:43,082 --> 00:16:44,849
Good night.

183
00:16:44,849 --> 00:16:46,373
Thought you had a team dinner.

184
00:16:46,373 --> 00:16:49,109
You're back early.

185
00:16:49,109 --> 00:16:52,609
I came early because
I wanted another drink with you.

186
00:16:52,609 --> 00:16:54,429
Got plans?

187
00:16:54,429 --> 00:16:58,089
Yeah. Something came up.

188
00:17:00,942 --> 00:17:02,993
What's with you?

189
00:17:02,993 --> 00:17:04,316
Meeting a guy?

190
00:17:04,316 --> 00:17:08,600
If you are, shouldn't you change
your underwear first?

191
00:17:08,600 --> 00:17:10,710
Must be something important.

192
00:17:10,710 --> 00:17:12,047
A film company.

193
00:17:12,047 --> 00:17:15,016
I have a script meeting.

194
00:17:17,873 --> 00:17:20,993
Doesn't sound like a film company.

195
00:17:21,712 --> 00:17:26,406
You know I have to show up sometimes,
even when I don't want to.

196
00:17:26,406 --> 00:17:29,879
So I'd appreciate it if you stopped asking.

197
00:17:33,273 --> 00:17:35,819
Okay.

198
00:17:37,640 --> 00:17:40,286
Sorry.

199
00:17:45,410 --> 00:17:48,163
Yeah, I'm heading out now.

200
00:17:51,122 --> 00:17:54,168
- Let's talk later.
- Okay.

201
00:18:18,461 --> 00:18:22,680
[The Nam Hye Hoon List]

202
00:18:23,688 --> 00:18:26,222
[Social Media Chat Analysis Report]

203
00:18:31,897 --> 00:18:35,308
[Receipt for Full Payment of Property Purchase]

204
00:18:35,308 --> 00:18:36,994
[Response to Request for
Access to Personal Information]

205
00:18:36,994 --> 00:18:39,131
Nam Hye Hoon's image was in free fall

206
00:18:39,131 --> 00:18:42,517
because of slush funds
and real estate speculation...

207
00:18:42,517 --> 00:18:43,436
[Suspected Backdoor Ties
Between Mayor Nam and WR Group]

208
00:18:43,436 --> 00:18:45,768
But after teaming up with WR recently,

209
00:18:45,768 --> 00:18:49,401
she suddenly rose
as a leading presidential contender.

210
00:18:50,781 --> 00:18:53,961
Especially... Lee Yang Mi.

211
00:18:53,961 --> 00:18:56,186
Who's the real power at WR these days?

212
00:18:56,186 --> 00:18:57,690
[WR Group Owner Kwon Se Myeong and His Wife,
Lee Yang Mi: Korea's No. 3 Conglomerate]

213
00:18:57,690 --> 00:19:00,663
It's Lee Yang Mi.

214
00:19:06,941 --> 00:19:09,820
[Sansugapsan]
Excuse me, do you have a table?

215
00:19:09,820 --> 00:19:11,844
Sorry, we're closed today.

216
00:19:11,844 --> 00:19:12,929
What?

217
00:19:12,929 --> 00:19:14,646
But it's not your day off.

218
00:19:14,646 --> 00:19:17,423
- Did someone rent out the whole place?
- Yes, they did.

219
00:19:17,423 --> 00:19:19,060
- What?
- I'm sorry.

220
00:19:19,060 --> 00:19:20,181
Let's go somewhere else.

221
00:19:20,181 --> 00:19:22,633
- Sorry about that.
- Okay.

222
00:19:34,907 --> 00:19:37,626
How's the atmosphere on set?

223
00:19:37,626 --> 00:19:40,333
You're doing well, right?

224
00:19:41,059 --> 00:19:42,916
Even if the director's a nobody,

225
00:19:42,916 --> 00:19:44,253
I read the script myself.

226
00:19:44,253 --> 00:19:47,053
It won't flop.

227
00:19:48,495 --> 00:19:50,473
Of course.

228
00:19:50,473 --> 00:19:54,413
It's my comeback project,
and you were the one who introduced it.

229
00:19:54,413 --> 00:19:57,293
I'll give it my all.

230
00:20:01,100 --> 00:20:03,044
Right.

231
00:20:03,044 --> 00:20:06,097
If you're born an actor
and will die an actor anyway,

232
00:20:06,097 --> 00:20:08,134
you've got to stay cool

233
00:20:08,134 --> 00:20:09,671
about a fate that swings like Tesla stock

234
00:20:09,671 --> 00:20:13,380
if you want to last in the long run.

235
00:20:16,229 --> 00:20:18,280
True.

236
00:20:18,280 --> 00:20:20,138
I tell myself it's all part of life's lessons

237
00:20:20,138 --> 00:20:23,659
and try not to ride the highs and lows...

238
00:20:23,659 --> 00:20:26,723
but in this industry,
that's easier said than done.

239
00:20:26,723 --> 00:20:28,553
Then again,

240
00:20:28,553 --> 00:20:31,780
I never liked the fate of entertainers
getting swept up by trends,

241
00:20:31,780 --> 00:20:35,470
living and dying by every rise and fall.

242
00:20:35,470 --> 00:20:36,855
With this face,

243
00:20:36,855 --> 00:20:40,855
I gave up on becoming an actress pretty early.

244
00:20:41,988 --> 00:20:43,913
I'm a Scorpio,

245
00:20:43,913 --> 00:20:48,619
so I prefer pulling the strings,
not being pulled.

246
00:20:53,015 --> 00:20:54,378
And you...

247
00:20:54,378 --> 00:20:58,918
Before you crashed,
you stayed on top thanks to me.

248
00:21:02,017 --> 00:21:06,497
Anyway, I've bought shares in your agency,

249
00:21:06,497 --> 00:21:10,023
and you're not getting any younger.

250
00:21:10,023 --> 00:21:14,076
Did you really think
I'd just let you fade away like this?

251
00:21:27,716 --> 00:21:30,709
So...

252
00:21:30,709 --> 00:21:31,812
I do have one card

253
00:21:31,812 --> 00:21:34,322
that could put you right back
on top in one shot.

254
00:21:34,322 --> 00:21:36,180
Lee Yang Mi...

255
00:21:36,180 --> 00:21:38,058
[Growing Favoritism Allegations]
She's the one who stirred things up

256
00:21:38,058 --> 00:21:40,128
with the Chief Prosecutor
and got me forced out.

257
00:21:40,128 --> 00:21:42,234
Mayor Nam's approval ratings were dropping,

258
00:21:42,234 --> 00:21:43,857
but her image turned around

259
00:21:43,857 --> 00:21:45,887
right after she started appearing
with Lee Yang Mi,

260
00:21:45,887 --> 00:21:49,160
the one who pulls the strings in the media.

261
00:21:49,906 --> 00:21:51,957
I knew she was bankrolling films and dramas

262
00:21:51,957 --> 00:21:56,045
and meeting celebrities through that,

263
00:21:56,045 --> 00:21:58,351
but I didn't realize her reach
extended into politics too.

264
00:21:58,351 --> 00:22:01,264
Exactly.

265
00:22:01,264 --> 00:22:04,461
So someone like Lee Yang Mi chose Nam Hye Hoon

266
00:22:04,461 --> 00:22:06,859
as her presidential partner?

267
00:22:06,859 --> 00:22:09,002
Yeah.

268
00:22:09,627 --> 00:22:13,798
But apparently she has a certain way
of doing business in politics.

269
00:22:13,798 --> 00:22:16,603
She brings in celebrities she has leverage over

270
00:22:16,603 --> 00:22:20,568
and uses them for sexual favors.

271
00:22:22,381 --> 00:22:24,312
Sang Ah.

272
00:22:24,312 --> 00:22:29,525
That rising actor your agency signed
with CEO Eom.

273
00:22:30,820 --> 00:22:33,480
Bae Yun Seong.

274
00:22:33,480 --> 00:22:35,230
Mayor Nam says

275
00:22:35,230 --> 00:22:38,520
watching his drama these days
is the highlight of her day.

276
00:22:38,520 --> 00:22:42,827
She keeps saying she wants to meet him.

277
00:22:42,827 --> 00:22:44,576
You know...

278
00:22:44,576 --> 00:22:46,720
We signed up for treatments
at Director Park's aesthetic clinic,

279
00:22:46,720 --> 00:22:48,068
and guess what.

280
00:22:48,068 --> 00:22:51,511
She wrote her nickname down as "Kim Byul."

281
00:22:51,511 --> 00:22:53,897
Funny, right?

282
00:22:54,672 --> 00:22:59,138
That's the name of
Yun Seong's co-star, isn't it?

283
00:23:07,130 --> 00:23:09,837
It is, right?

284
00:23:10,857 --> 00:23:13,943
- Director...
- Or am I wrong?

285
00:23:14,836 --> 00:23:18,063
Don't go that far.

286
00:23:19,431 --> 00:23:20,948
What?

287
00:23:20,948 --> 00:23:23,608
You should be satisfied with just me.

288
00:23:23,608 --> 00:23:26,954
Leave the agency and Yun Seong out of it.

289
00:23:30,989 --> 00:23:33,849
Listen, Chu Sang Ah.

290
00:23:34,783 --> 00:23:37,662
Get a grip.

291
00:23:40,917 --> 00:23:43,367
You're not stupid.

292
00:23:43,367 --> 00:23:46,986
You said you wanted your top spot back.

293
00:23:46,986 --> 00:23:50,017
Whether you sink lower or climb back up
depends on me.

294
00:23:50,017 --> 00:23:53,043
So face reality.

295
00:23:53,043 --> 00:23:55,330
In a situation like this...

296
00:23:55,330 --> 00:23:59,103
This isn't the time
to be clinging to your pride.

297
00:24:06,382 --> 00:24:10,886
If you take one more step, it is a cliff.

298
00:24:10,886 --> 00:24:12,690
You see that, right?

299
00:24:12,690 --> 00:24:14,407
Whether you keep going or not...

300
00:24:14,407 --> 00:24:17,306
That's your call.

301
00:24:32,914 --> 00:24:35,787
Did you drink a lot?

302
00:24:37,088 --> 00:24:39,575
No.

303
00:24:39,575 --> 00:24:42,234
I think I just feel sick.

304
00:24:44,581 --> 00:24:47,261
Did something happen?

305
00:24:47,261 --> 00:24:50,161
Just a little rough.

306
00:24:59,551 --> 00:25:02,311
Are we...

307
00:25:02,311 --> 00:25:05,224
going to be okay?

308
00:25:19,914 --> 00:25:22,873
I'm sorry.

309
00:25:24,647 --> 00:25:28,547
I feel like I'm not much help to you.

310
00:25:32,787 --> 00:25:36,020
Don't say that.

311
00:25:38,610 --> 00:25:41,750
Honestly, today was hard.

312
00:25:43,537 --> 00:25:47,283
I know I can go further,

313
00:25:49,130 --> 00:25:51,849
but I'm scared

314
00:25:52,956 --> 00:25:56,176
this might be the end for me.

315
00:26:04,803 --> 00:26:06,920
Do you know why

316
00:26:06,920 --> 00:26:10,106
I wanted to be with you so badly?

317
00:26:11,067 --> 00:26:14,957
Even when you get hurt and knocked down,

318
00:26:14,957 --> 00:26:18,163
even when you're afraid,

319
00:26:18,937 --> 00:26:22,237
you're the kind of woman

320
00:26:22,237 --> 00:26:25,963
who's more afraid of stopping
than anything else.

321
00:26:26,709 --> 00:26:29,217
That's what I admired

322
00:26:29,217 --> 00:26:31,850
about you.

323
00:26:43,018 --> 00:26:45,918
I feel the same.

324
00:26:46,585 --> 00:26:49,272
With you...

325
00:26:49,272 --> 00:26:53,071
I thought I could go all the way.

326
00:26:53,951 --> 00:26:56,658
That's why.

327
00:27:10,809 --> 00:27:13,602
You know, I threw up.

328
00:27:59,282 --> 00:28:03,809
When I look at the woman,
it feels like I'm looking at myself.

329
00:28:03,809 --> 00:28:06,703
That's why I wanted to have her.

330
00:28:06,703 --> 00:28:10,483
And I thought I did...

331
00:28:10,483 --> 00:28:12,863
But lately,

332
00:28:12,863 --> 00:28:16,509
I'm starting to think
maybe that was just my illusion.

333
00:28:17,296 --> 00:28:20,215
You're madly in love with her.

334
00:28:21,926 --> 00:28:24,224
This isn't the place

335
00:28:24,224 --> 00:28:27,899
to go on about your tragic love story.

336
00:28:29,304 --> 00:28:32,587
I don't have anywhere else
to talk about my wife.

337
00:28:32,587 --> 00:28:34,873
Sorry.

338
00:28:36,067 --> 00:28:39,120
No need to apologize.

339
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:43,513
These are files on Lee Yang Mi
and Nam Hye Hoon.

340
00:28:46,158 --> 00:28:48,801
They really are close.

341
00:28:48,801 --> 00:28:50,098
Even with their busy schedules,

342
00:28:50,098 --> 00:28:52,171
whether it's golf or the aesthetic clinic...

343
00:28:52,171 --> 00:28:55,211
they always show up together.

344
00:28:56,057 --> 00:28:57,828
And...

345
00:28:57,828 --> 00:28:59,913
the SBC vice chairman
and the Doyak Party leader

346
00:28:59,913 --> 00:29:01,813
arrived one after another,

347
00:29:01,813 --> 00:29:04,764
took the elevator up,
and got off at the penthouse floor.

348
00:29:04,764 --> 00:29:06,481
Soon after, a group of women arrived

349
00:29:06,481 --> 00:29:08,214
and got off on the same floor.

350
00:29:08,214 --> 00:29:11,694
I couldn't get a clear look,

351
00:29:11,694 --> 00:29:15,254
but they looked like recognizable celebrities.

352
00:29:16,567 --> 00:29:18,658
Interesting.

353
00:29:18,658 --> 00:29:21,484
And this is

354
00:29:22,184 --> 00:29:24,481
the WR Hotel reservation list.

355
00:29:24,481 --> 00:29:26,421
[Hotel Room Reservation Log]
See the name "Kim Byul?"

356
00:29:26,421 --> 00:29:29,425
That's the name Nam Hye Hoon uses
when she books aesthetic appointments.

357
00:29:29,425 --> 00:29:32,425
Next Wednesday.

358
00:29:32,425 --> 00:29:34,665
Okay.

359
00:29:37,925 --> 00:29:39,895
This case...

360
00:29:39,895 --> 00:29:41,566
Finish it well.

361
00:29:41,566 --> 00:29:45,551
Once it's done, I'll throw in a little extra.

362
00:30:00,426 --> 00:30:03,063
Looks like you're really quitting your job.

363
00:30:03,063 --> 00:30:06,451
You should stop playing informant for me too.

364
00:30:06,451 --> 00:30:09,697
I'll find you something else.

365
00:30:11,083 --> 00:30:14,781
I'll handle my own life, so stay out of it.

366
00:30:14,781 --> 00:30:18,491
How am I supposed to stay out of your life?

367
00:30:18,491 --> 00:30:19,942
If you can't...

368
00:30:19,942 --> 00:30:22,452
It's not like you'd choose me over Chu Sang Ah.

369
00:30:22,452 --> 00:30:24,858
I'm heading out.

370
00:30:39,818 --> 00:30:42,614
[CINE24]

371
00:30:47,357 --> 00:30:48,733
Tae Seop.

372
00:30:48,733 --> 00:30:49,987
Yes, sir.

373
00:30:49,987 --> 00:30:51,272
I hear

374
00:30:51,272 --> 00:30:53,506
you've been making quite a name
for yourself lately.

375
00:30:53,506 --> 00:30:55,439
Sorry?

376
00:31:00,691 --> 00:31:03,604
Word is you've been sticking your nose

377
00:31:03,604 --> 00:31:07,814
where it doesn't belong.

378
00:31:07,814 --> 00:31:12,140
Decided to start living life on the edge?

379
00:31:14,039 --> 00:31:16,672
Mayor Nam Hye Hoon.

380
00:31:16,672 --> 00:31:19,892
I hear you've been digging into her lately.

381
00:31:19,892 --> 00:31:21,776
Oh, that's just...

382
00:31:21,776 --> 00:31:23,170
You little punk!

383
00:31:23,170 --> 00:31:25,195
If I miss that deputy chief promotion again,

384
00:31:25,195 --> 00:31:28,862
are you going to take responsibility for it?

385
00:31:28,862 --> 00:31:31,147
What on earth are you doing?

386
00:31:31,147 --> 00:31:32,738
The personnel announcement is coming up.

387
00:31:32,738 --> 00:31:36,108
Are you trying to drag us all down with you?

388
00:31:36,108 --> 00:31:37,718
Listen.

389
00:31:37,718 --> 00:31:39,639
If you want to get yourself killed,
do it alone.

390
00:31:39,639 --> 00:31:42,525
Why are you splashing your mess all over me?

391
00:31:42,525 --> 00:31:44,549
Sir, this is a misunderstanding.

392
00:31:44,549 --> 00:31:46,939
I was only checking something I heard.

393
00:31:46,939 --> 00:31:48,789
Checking?

394
00:31:48,789 --> 00:31:50,562
You little jerk...

395
00:31:50,562 --> 00:31:52,475
Hey.

396
00:31:52,475 --> 00:31:55,346
Who do you think you are,
checking up on Mayor Nam?

397
00:31:55,346 --> 00:31:56,790
Why? Why?

398
00:31:56,790 --> 00:31:59,223
Darn it.

399
00:32:00,580 --> 00:32:03,280
This is really irritating.

400
00:32:17,228 --> 00:32:20,486
Even this bastard's cousin is a congressman.

401
00:32:20,486 --> 00:32:22,162
If the prosecution gets purged,

402
00:32:22,162 --> 00:32:24,756
guys like me will be the first to go.

403
00:32:24,756 --> 00:32:27,573
Drop the Mayor Nam case right now.

404
00:32:27,573 --> 00:32:29,143
Got it?

405
00:32:29,143 --> 00:32:30,774
Of course. Much respect, sir.

406
00:32:30,774 --> 00:32:32,826
Darn it.

407
00:32:37,332 --> 00:32:39,779
That's not going to...

408
00:32:39,779 --> 00:32:41,898
work for me.

409
00:32:45,204 --> 00:32:47,835
My way out is already gone,

410
00:32:47,835 --> 00:32:51,495
so I might as well go all in.

411
00:33:18,226 --> 00:33:22,180
I heard they call you the Doberman of
the Seoam Central District Prosecution.

412
00:33:22,180 --> 00:33:25,267
I actually keep a Doberman myself.

413
00:33:26,900 --> 00:33:30,273
Is that why you went after Chu Sang Ah too?

414
00:33:31,100 --> 00:33:34,154
I can't exactly deny that.

415
00:33:34,154 --> 00:33:35,831
Go ahead.

416
00:33:35,831 --> 00:33:38,531
I'm on a diet.

417
00:33:49,012 --> 00:33:50,309
Kwon Jong Uk.

418
00:33:50,309 --> 00:33:52,239
The heir to WR Group,

419
00:33:52,239 --> 00:33:54,459
the third-largest company
in Korea by market cap.

420
00:33:54,459 --> 00:33:56,656
He's been raised with a silver spoon.

421
00:33:56,656 --> 00:34:01,089
All pride and not a shred of common sense.

422
00:34:01,089 --> 00:34:03,080
Kwon Se Myeong, the owner of WR,

423
00:34:03,080 --> 00:34:04,981
and his wife, Director Lee Yang Mi.

424
00:34:04,981 --> 00:34:06,331
Then there are the twin sons

425
00:34:06,331 --> 00:34:07,878
from Kwon Se Myeong's previous marriage.

426
00:34:07,878 --> 00:34:10,320
Kwon Jong Uk and Kwon Jong Il.

427
00:34:10,320 --> 00:34:12,863
When the younger brother, Kwon Jong Il,
gave up his claim to management,

428
00:34:12,863 --> 00:34:16,238
WR was practically Jong Uk's for the taking.

429
00:34:16,238 --> 00:34:18,575
But then Lee Yang Mi gave birth
to Kwon Se Myeong's daughter.

430
00:34:18,575 --> 00:34:20,886
She secured control of the hotel
and entertainment divisions,

431
00:34:20,886 --> 00:34:25,966
and that is when the real war
between her and Kwon Jong Uk began.

432
00:34:25,966 --> 00:34:28,579
So far, the score is two to one.

433
00:34:28,579 --> 00:34:30,276
Lee Yang Mi is the one with two.

434
00:34:30,276 --> 00:34:33,453
Which means if I take down Nam Hye Hoon
and it hits Lee Yang Mi as well,

435
00:34:33,453 --> 00:34:35,270
the one who benefits the most

436
00:34:35,270 --> 00:34:36,467
is this man.

437
00:34:36,467 --> 00:34:40,957
It sounded like an interesting offer,
so I came.

438
00:34:40,957 --> 00:34:43,327
But how exactly are you planning

439
00:34:43,327 --> 00:34:46,960
to take down Lee Yang Mi through Nam Hye Hoon?

440
00:34:48,307 --> 00:34:50,078
Soon, Lee Yang Mi will be making

441
00:34:50,078 --> 00:34:54,011
an illegal lobbying move on
Mayor Nam at the WR Hotel.

442
00:34:54,902 --> 00:34:58,807
I'll raid the scene and take Mayor Nam down.

443
00:34:58,807 --> 00:35:02,613
When that happens,
Lee Yang Mi's grand plan falls apart too.

444
00:35:07,530 --> 00:35:10,050
That is sexy.

445
00:35:13,846 --> 00:35:17,932
So you must want something from me
for coming all this way.

446
00:35:23,928 --> 00:35:28,285
Make sure the story breaks
and does not get buried.

447
00:35:28,285 --> 00:35:31,575
And back me for the nomination
in the upcoming general election.

448
00:35:31,575 --> 00:35:34,182
You want my backing?

449
00:35:34,182 --> 00:35:35,879
That's not hard.

450
00:35:35,879 --> 00:35:37,999
But,

451
00:35:39,119 --> 00:35:41,785
we just met.

452
00:35:41,785 --> 00:35:45,331
Why should I trust you?

453
00:35:46,819 --> 00:35:49,483
I never asked you to trust me.

454
00:35:49,483 --> 00:35:52,944
You need Lee Yang Mi taken down
without getting blood on your hands

455
00:35:52,944 --> 00:35:54,616
if you want to protect WR.

456
00:35:54,616 --> 00:35:56,433
And I need Mayor Nam taken down

457
00:35:56,433 --> 00:35:59,083
to clear my path to the general election.

458
00:35:59,083 --> 00:36:00,227
Is there

459
00:36:00,227 --> 00:36:02,013
any bond stronger than

460
00:36:02,013 --> 00:36:04,993
two people whose interests align?

461
00:36:07,762 --> 00:36:10,445
You and I...

462
00:36:10,445 --> 00:36:12,622
see the world the same way.

463
00:36:12,622 --> 00:36:15,555
You're a strategist, huh?

464
00:36:16,855 --> 00:36:19,859
Seems like a waste to stop
at the general election with you.

465
00:36:19,859 --> 00:36:21,883
The general election is not my goal.

466
00:36:21,883 --> 00:36:25,952
My goal is to stand at the top of Korea.

467
00:36:34,812 --> 00:36:36,729
Now that is some ambition.

468
00:36:36,729 --> 00:36:38,973
Protect WR Group.

469
00:36:38,973 --> 00:36:42,253
And keep working with me.

470
00:36:45,260 --> 00:36:47,667
Bravo.

471
00:36:56,995 --> 00:37:00,841
I heard you met Director Lee Yang Mi.

472
00:37:04,251 --> 00:37:06,264
Yeah.

473
00:37:08,251 --> 00:37:10,562
Then I guess you heard about

474
00:37:10,562 --> 00:37:13,362
Yun Seong too.

475
00:37:15,046 --> 00:37:16,741
How did you know?

476
00:37:16,741 --> 00:37:20,309
WR's director office contacted us.

477
00:37:24,241 --> 00:37:26,265
Don't worry about it.

478
00:37:26,265 --> 00:37:28,615
It is nothing like that.

479
00:37:28,615 --> 00:37:31,035
I expected something like this

480
00:37:31,035 --> 00:37:34,855
when Director Lee bought shares
in our company.

481
00:37:36,099 --> 00:37:39,486
This really sucks.

482
00:37:40,720 --> 00:37:43,520
Yeah, it does.

483
00:37:46,246 --> 00:37:48,432
By the way,

484
00:37:48,432 --> 00:37:52,292
do you know why I bought shares in your agency?

485
00:37:52,292 --> 00:37:54,699
What, because I felt sorry for you?

486
00:37:54,699 --> 00:37:56,645
No.

487
00:37:56,645 --> 00:37:58,782
I'm not a charity worker.

488
00:37:58,782 --> 00:38:00,806
I'm a businesswoman.

489
00:38:00,806 --> 00:38:03,196
Do you think I'd invest that kind of money

490
00:38:03,196 --> 00:38:05,889
without anything to gain?

491
00:38:05,889 --> 00:38:07,586
Are you threatening me right now?

492
00:38:07,586 --> 00:38:09,615
I'm offering you a deal.

493
00:38:09,615 --> 00:38:12,649
Let's call it even with this.

494
00:38:14,156 --> 00:38:19,533
Whether you end up shredded
in my blender as the sacrificial lamb,

495
00:38:19,533 --> 00:38:22,863
or survive and step back onto the stage,

496
00:38:22,863 --> 00:38:26,163
that's entirely up to you.

497
00:38:32,708 --> 00:38:34,652
Oh, if that sounded like a threat,

498
00:38:34,652 --> 00:38:36,912
sorry.

499
00:38:51,167 --> 00:38:54,026
Let's find another way.

500
00:38:55,928 --> 00:38:59,471
I can't make a comeback using
a dirty trick like that.

501
00:38:59,471 --> 00:39:04,684
And Yun Seong will become a star soon anyway.

502
00:39:06,881 --> 00:39:09,785
So even if Lee Yang Mi's side reaches out,

503
00:39:09,785 --> 00:39:13,098
don't touch Yun Seong.

504
00:39:15,121 --> 00:39:17,840
Understood?

505
00:39:19,754 --> 00:39:22,592
All right.

506
00:39:35,783 --> 00:39:38,596
Hello, director.

507
00:39:39,656 --> 00:39:41,150
Hey, leave that.

508
00:39:41,150 --> 00:39:43,103
The energy is off today.
That color works better.

509
00:39:43,103 --> 00:39:45,389
Understood.

510
00:39:50,596 --> 00:39:52,313
This scent doesn't suit the lobby today.

511
00:39:52,313 --> 00:39:53,553
Then...

512
00:39:53,553 --> 00:39:55,578
which scent would you prefer?

513
00:39:55,578 --> 00:39:58,923
Patchouli's woody note adds
a more refined mood,

514
00:39:58,923 --> 00:40:03,096
and the warm trail of ambergris
gives it a sensual finish.

515
00:40:03,096 --> 00:40:05,481
Clear that one out.

516
00:40:05,481 --> 00:40:08,668
Who is this VVIP coming today?

517
00:40:08,668 --> 00:40:11,187
The mayor.

518
00:40:12,047 --> 00:40:13,771
Welcome, ma'am.

519
00:40:13,771 --> 00:40:16,447
- Yeah.
- This way, please.

520
00:40:43,362 --> 00:40:48,602
Whether you end up shredded
in my blender as the sacrificial lamb,

521
00:40:48,602 --> 00:40:51,739
or survive and step back onto the stage,

522
00:40:51,739 --> 00:40:54,952
that's entirely up to you.

523
00:40:54,952 --> 00:40:57,021
Sang Ah.

524
00:41:00,538 --> 00:41:03,541
I was supposed to meet CEO Eom. Where is he?

525
00:41:03,541 --> 00:41:05,025
Well... about that...

526
00:41:05,025 --> 00:41:07,861
He said something suddenly came up.

527
00:41:07,861 --> 00:41:10,307
What do you mean?

528
00:41:31,449 --> 00:41:32,519
Hey, Sang Ah.

529
00:41:32,519 --> 00:41:33,665
Where are you?

530
00:41:33,665 --> 00:41:35,676
I'm just...

531
00:41:35,676 --> 00:41:38,095
Well...

532
00:41:38,095 --> 00:41:41,326
I didn't want to do this either.

533
00:41:41,326 --> 00:41:42,536
But

534
00:41:42,536 --> 00:41:43,753
Director Lee's office...

535
00:41:43,753 --> 00:41:46,583
They are coming down hard,
saying they will pull their investment.

536
00:41:46,583 --> 00:41:48,660
Our company is already
struggling as it is, you know.

537
00:41:48,660 --> 00:41:50,157
Are you insane?

538
00:41:50,157 --> 00:41:53,030
You still can't go through with this.

539
00:41:53,030 --> 00:41:55,114
What did Yun Seong ever do wrong?

540
00:41:55,114 --> 00:41:58,371
He agreed to it.

541
00:41:58,371 --> 00:41:59,398
What?

542
00:41:59,398 --> 00:42:01,058
Yun Seong said

543
00:42:01,058 --> 00:42:04,848
there is a limit to the roles he can land
through auditions.

544
00:42:04,848 --> 00:42:05,966
And once this is over,

545
00:42:05,966 --> 00:42:09,842
WR will cast him as the lead
in a romcom they're producing.

546
00:42:09,842 --> 00:42:12,429
So yeah, Yun Seong was the one
who said he'd do it first.

547
00:42:13,171 --> 00:42:15,129
Don't worry.

548
00:42:15,129 --> 00:42:18,415
He is ambitious, you know.

549
00:42:22,669 --> 00:42:24,166
Let's go to the WR Hotel.

550
00:42:24,166 --> 00:42:26,109
Yes.

551
00:42:30,213 --> 00:42:32,183
Today's recommendation is

552
00:42:32,183 --> 00:42:34,766
a premium vintage from Lafano Winery.

553
00:42:34,766 --> 00:42:38,799
It has a spicy profile with a firm, full body.

554
00:42:46,291 --> 00:42:49,091
Enjoy your evening.

555
00:43:41,628 --> 00:43:43,912
[Bae Yun Seong]

556
00:43:47,566 --> 00:43:50,490
The call can't be completed. Please leave...

557
00:45:14,313 --> 00:45:18,093
Penthouse, 17th floor. Target is in.

558
00:46:43,559 --> 00:46:45,790
I'm by the back entrance...

559
00:46:45,790 --> 00:46:49,063
Chu Sang Ah is here.

560
00:46:49,689 --> 00:46:52,101
What are you talking about?
You sure you didn't see wrong?

561
00:46:52,101 --> 00:46:53,172
No.

562
00:46:53,172 --> 00:46:56,513
You know my eyes don't miss things.

563
00:47:23,256 --> 00:47:26,115
Yun Seong.

564
00:47:26,115 --> 00:47:28,482
Sang Ah?

565
00:48:07,053 --> 00:48:09,853
You have to go in, Sang Ah.

566
00:48:18,530 --> 00:48:21,516
All it takes is closing your eyes once,

567
00:48:21,516 --> 00:48:24,763
and you will be a star.

568
00:49:14,251 --> 00:49:16,797
Let's go.

569
00:49:20,568 --> 00:49:22,965
I'm really sorry.

570
00:49:22,965 --> 00:49:26,445
I'll just close my eyes once and come back.

571
00:49:49,383 --> 00:49:52,982
Hello, ma'am. I'm Bae Yun Seong.

572
00:49:52,982 --> 00:49:54,644
Oh, there you are.

573
00:49:54,644 --> 00:49:58,397
You're even cuter in person.

574
00:49:58,397 --> 00:49:59,754
Come sit here.

575
00:49:59,754 --> 00:50:01,694
Yes.

576
00:51:05,975 --> 00:51:07,679
Close your eyes

577
00:51:07,679 --> 00:51:10,106
just once tonight,

578
00:51:10,106 --> 00:51:13,339
and you'll be a star.

579
00:51:42,024 --> 00:51:45,217
The call can't be completed. Please leave...

580
00:51:46,489 --> 00:51:50,229
[Bang Tae Seop]

581
00:53:53,904 --> 00:53:56,844
Try calling me Byul.

582
00:53:58,197 --> 00:53:59,814
Byul.

583
00:53:59,814 --> 00:54:02,534
Oh, Kim Byul.

584
00:54:13,230 --> 00:54:14,681
Kim Byul.

585
00:54:15,328 --> 00:54:17,594
Call me Byul.

586
00:54:17,594 --> 00:54:20,808
Byul... Byul...

587
00:54:22,600 --> 00:54:25,881
Hello, Mayor Nam Hye Hoon.

588
00:54:26,821 --> 00:54:29,372
What the... Who are you?

589
00:54:29,372 --> 00:54:30,809
Who are you?

590
00:54:30,809 --> 00:54:32,707
Hey!

591
00:54:32,707 --> 00:54:34,352
I'm sorry. Please let me go!

592
00:54:34,352 --> 00:54:37,668
Is anyone out there?

593
00:54:57,355 --> 00:54:59,840
[Hong Jin Kyu]
[CEO of Big Entertainment]

594
00:54:59,840 --> 00:55:03,426
[9 years earlier]

595
00:58:14,000 --> 00:58:15,744
This is a good film.

596
00:58:15,744 --> 00:58:17,672
It's a shame it will never be released.

597
00:58:17,672 --> 00:58:20,844
Do you have any idea

598
00:58:20,844 --> 00:58:22,339
who's holding the keys right now?

599
00:58:22,339 --> 00:58:24,918
This was done without consulting me.

600
00:58:24,918 --> 00:58:27,269
That's your fault too.

601
00:58:27,269 --> 00:58:31,158
From now on, you work for me.

602
00:58:31,158 --> 00:58:33,355
Are you hiding something from me these days?

603
00:58:33,355 --> 00:58:34,958
No.

604
00:58:34,958 --> 00:58:37,296
My wife is hiding something.

605
00:58:37,296 --> 00:58:39,515
Wiretap her or follow her.

606
00:58:39,515 --> 00:58:41,265
Just dig into it for me.

607
00:58:41,265 --> 00:58:42,745
Please.

608
00:58:42,745 --> 00:58:44,402
If you go any further with this...

609
00:58:44,402 --> 00:58:46,955
you and I are finished.

610
00:58:46,955 --> 00:58:49,892
You might be opening Pandora's box.

611
00:58:49,892 --> 00:58:53,245
If it is a box that will be opened anyway...

612
00:58:53,245 --> 00:58:56,918
then it might as well be me who opens it first.
